#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Introducing Quarkus Agent MCP: teaching AI agents to speak Quarkus"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: synopsis
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Quarkus Agent MCP is a standalone MCP server that lets AI coding agents create, manage, and work effectively with Quarkus applications. Extension authors can ship coding skills that agents pick up automatically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"AI coding agents like Claude Code, GitHub Copilot, Cursor, Windsurf, and JetBrains AI are already capable of generating code, fixing bugs, and refactoring entire modules.\n"
"But they become much more effective when they have context about the framework you are using: that Quarkus dev mode hot-reloads on the next request rather than on file save, that Panache entities need `@Transactional` for writes, that REST clients should be injected via CDI rather than instantiated manually."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus-agent-mcp[Quarkus Agent MCP] gives agents exactly that context.\n"
"It is a standalone https://modelcontextprotocol.io[MCP (Model Context Protocol)] server that lets any compatible AI agent create, manage, and work effectively with Quarkus applications by providing Quarkus-specific tools, documentation, and extension-level coding patterns."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "What is MCP?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"The https://modelcontextprotocol.io[Model Context Protocol] is an open standard that lets AI agents discover and use tools exposed by external servers.\n"
"Instead of hard-coding integrations for every framework, an agent connects to MCP servers that provide domain-specific capabilities.\n"
"The agent discovers available tools at runtime and calls them as needed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "It's a plugin system for AI agents: connect to a server and the agent gains new capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid "Why a standalone server?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"Quarkus already has a built-in Dev MCP server that exposes tools from inside a running application: endpoints, configuration, dev services, testing, and more.\n"
"So why add another server?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"The answer is *lifecycle*.\n"
"The built-in Dev MCP server lives inside the Quarkus process.\n"
"When the app crashes (a compilation error, a missing bean, a bad migration), that MCP server dies with it.\n"
"The agent loses its connection and cannot inspect what went wrong."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-07-introducing-agent-mcp.adoc
msgid ""
"Quarkus Agent MCP runs as a separate process.\n"
"It wraps `quarkus dev` as a child process and stays alive when the application crashes.\n"
"The agent can read the logs, get structured exception details, fix the code, and watch the app recover on its own."
msgstr ""

